<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' ROUNDUP; SANTA MARGARITA ERASES 15-POINT DEFICIT TO STUN TUSTIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Santa Margarita rallied from a 15-point deficit to overcome Tustin, 54-50, in 
a Sea View League girls' basketball game Thursday at Tustin. 
</P>
<P>
 Shannon Noonan scored 14 points, 12 in the second half, for Santa Margarita 
(4-11, 2-5 in league). Susie Dionne had 18 and Kelly Moohr added 12 for Santa 
Margarita. Tustin is 12-7, 4-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin led, 30-15, at the half, but Santa Margarita outscored the Tillers, 
22-13, in the third quarter and, 17-7, in the fourth quarter using an up-tempo 
offense and a pressure defense. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Sea View League games: 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 85, Saddleback 23 -- All five starters scored in double figures for 
second-ranked Woodbridge. Erin Stovall had a game-high 17 points for the 
Warriors (18-0, 7-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 58, University 44 -- Eighth-ranked Newport Harbor (13-5, 6-1) 
got 21 points from Genevieve Evarts to remain in second place. Jennifer Stanley 
had a game-high 23 for University. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 54, Corona del Mar 47 -- Melinda Newe had 17 points, four assists and 
three steals for Irvine (9-7, 3-4). Meaghan Woodruff had 17 points for the 
Vaqueros. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Express League: 
</P>
<P>
 Heritage Christian 42, Rolling Hills Prep 18 -- Sheri Larson scored 18 points 
for Heritage Christian (9-5, 6-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 59, Sonora 58 -- Aiyanna Nash's desperation shot didn't beat the 
buzzer for Sonora. Nash finished with 20 points for Sonora (1-17, 0-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Troy 54, Sunny Hills 26 -- Jennie Gadd had 26 points for Warriors (13-5, 5-0), 
who remained in first place. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 37, Buena Park 28 -- Nadia Hoerner scored 21 points for host 
Fullerton (11-7, 3-1), which led, 16-0, at the end of the first quarter. 
</P>
