 In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 54, Dana Hills 48 -- Ninth-ranked San Clemente (14-4, 4-1) 
defeated 10th-ranked Dana Hills (13-5, 3-2) to take sole possession of second 
place. Michelle Macintyre had a game-high 28 points for the Tritons. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 62, Capistrano Valley 46 -- Leticia Osegura had 19 points and Melody 
Peterson had 18 for fourth-ranked Mater Dei (15-2, 5-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Mission Viejo 51, El Toro 41 -- Treva Whitaker made 13 of 15 free throws in 
the fourth quarter to help visiting Mission Viejo (7-9, 1-4) hold off El Toro. 
Whitaker made 15 of 17 free throws in the game and finished with 24 points. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 52, Rosary 51 -- Marie Philman had nine of her game-high 27 points in 
the fourth quarter as host Edison held off Rosary (9-5, 3-4). Jennifer Chey 
made a three-pointer as time ran out for Rosary to make it a one-point game. 
Kathleen Celio had 19 and Chey 10. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina 69, Huntington Beach 66 -- Tied at the end of the half, Marina's change 
in defense was the turning point for the Vikings, who made eight steals and 
allowed only six points in the third quarter. Shandy Robbins had 21 points and 
18 rebounds and Traci Nakamura had a season-high of 17 points for No. 6 Marina 
(13-5, 6-1). 
</P>
