<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL; USC RALLIES TO BEAT ARIZONA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lisa Leslie scored 20 points and Nicky McCrimmon added 17 as ninth-ranked USC 
rallied from a 12-point second-half deficit to defeat Arizona, 76-65, Thursday 
night at Tucson. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing, 54-42, with 13:36 to play, the Trojans, 12-1 overall and 5-0 in the 
Pacific 10 Conference, took the lead for good at 59-58 and finished the run at 
61-58 on McCrimmon's steal and layup with 6:34 to play. Arizona (8-4, 2-2) was 
led by Kim Conway with 17 points. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA 84, Arizona State 59 -- Zrinka Kristich scored 20 points and had eight 
rebounds and Natalie Williams added 19 points and 10 rebounds as the Bruins 
(8-6, 3-2) won at Tempe, Ariz. The Sun Devils fell to 2-10 and 0-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
