<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN JOSE STATE DEFEATS FULLERTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton basketball Coach Brad Holland frowned as he looked at the 
statistics sheet after the Titans' 69-63 Big West Conference loss to San Jose 
State on Thursday night at Titan gym. 
</P>
<P>
 He wasn't looking at the score, but at the rebounding.San Jose State, the 
worst rebounding team in the conference, outrebounded Fullerton, 42-27, 
including 15-6 on the offensive end. 
</P>
<P>
 "Look at that," Holland said. "You tell me if rebounding was the difference in 
the game or not. We shot 43%, they shot 39%. We had only 10 turnovers. We just 
didn't rebound." 
</P>
<P>
 Terry Cannon, a 5-foot-11 guard, scored 16 points and pulled down eight 
rebounds as San Jose State, 7-7 and 3-3 in the Big West, won at Titan gym for 
the first time since 1984. 
</P>
<P>
 Forward Winston Peterson, strapped with foul trouble in the first half, scored 
18 of his game-high 23 points in the second half to lead the Titans (3-11, 
1-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton trailed, 25-18, at halftime. MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
