<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC EDGES UC IRVINE, 73-71 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine's DeForrest Boyer missed a falling-down, six-foot shot as time ran 
out and Pacific held on for a 73-71 Big West victory in front of 1,731 in the 
Bren Center.  
</P>
<P>
 The Anteaters, 5-8 and 2-3 in Big West, led by 16 early, were outscored, 23-0, 
midway through the game, fought back from a 10-point deficit with 3:42 to go 
and had the ball in Boyer's hands underneath the basket, trailing by two with 
2.3 seconds remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 "I believe I was fouled," Boyer said, "but they didn't blow the whistle, so 
it's over now." 
</P>
<P>
 "I kind of got him on the arm," Pacific guard Charles Terrell said, "but, hey, 
you have to play aggressive and the refs aren't going to see everything." 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific (10-7, 4-2) shot 70% in the second half after making 38% in the first 
half. JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
