<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOYOLA LOSES DESPITE JONES' 39 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gerald Walker's 20 points and Art Wallace's 19 points and 23 rebounds led the 
University of San Francisco to a 101-86 West Coast Conference victory over 
Loyola Marymount on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dons, 9-5 overall and 1-2 in the WCC, ran away with the victory despite 
Wyking Jones' 39 points and 16 rebounds for the Lions (1-13, 0-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson Stephens scored eight points to trigger a 14-4 run that turned a 13-13 
tie into a 27-17 USF lead with 10:30 remaining in the half. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dons' lead fluctuated between five and 12 points. USF led at the half, 
52-44. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lions came within three points at 55-52 and four points at 69-65 with 
11:40 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 Kent Bennett and Stephens each finished with 16 points for USF. 
</P>
