<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN BOOSTER MICELLI, 50, DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nicholas Micelli, father of Cal State Northridge basketball player Peter 
Micelli, was found dead in a Camarillo motel room on Thursday, apparently the 
victim of a heart attack. 
</P>
<P>
 Micelli, 50, a Beverly Hills attorney, was a loyal fan of the Matador 
basketball team, often attending road games. 
</P>
<P>
 Barry Smith, a school spokesman, said Micelli was en route to San Francisco to 
work on a case after stopping Wednesday in Northridge to deliver food and 
supplies to students displaced by Monday's earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 Micelli, is survived by his wife, Frances, son Peter and daughters Pauline and 
Maria. Funeral arrangements will be announced today. MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
