<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOWLING; HROMEK TAKES LEAD AT LAKEWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DON SNYDER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Justin Hromek of Andover, Kan. led comfortably after 26 games of the $220,000 
AC/Delco PBA Tournament Thursday night at Cal Bowl in Lakewood. 
</P>
<P>
 But popular sentiment seemed to be with Robert Smith, who graduated two years 
ago from Royal High School in Simi Valley and was in third place -- 65 pins 
behind the leader. 
</P>
<P>
 Hromek, seeking his second PBA title, won six of eight matches with a high 
game of 268 for a 5,913 total. 
</P>
<P>
 Parker Bohn III of Freehold, N.J., at 5,849, was second. Smith's total was 
5,848. Floridian Joe Firpo, at 5,828, was fourth and Mike Aulby of Indianapolis 
fifth at 5,815. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith, the only amateur in the competition, is a budding international star 
for the United States. He will be among members of Team USA at Colorado Springs 
later this month for Olympic training. 
</P>
<P>
 The field of 183 was cut to 24 earlier in the day after 18 games. 
</P>
<P>
 Aulby, Del Ballard Jr., Wayne Webb and David Ozio survived the cut. 
</P>
<P>
 Several favorites, however, didn't, including Walter Ray Williams Jr., Pete 
Weber, Brian Voss, Gary Dickinson and Marshal Holman. 
</P>
