EARTHQUAKE / THE LONG ROAD BACK; COLLEGE PLACEMENT TESTS POSTPONED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 College placement exams scheduled for 11 a.m. Saturday at Los Angeles-area 
sites have been postponed until February because of disruptions caused by 
Monday's quake, the Educational Testing Service announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The locations affected are: El Camino, Garfield, Hamilton, Los Angeles, 
Roosevelt, San Fernando, University and Van Nuys high schools in the Los 
Angeles Unified School District; Harvard-Westlake School in Studio City; Cal 
State Northridge, and Canyon High School in Santa Clarita. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 3,000 students were scheduled planned to take the Scholastic 
Aptitude Test or achievement tests at those sites. Educational Testing Service 
officials said students will be notified in writing of the date and site of 
their makeup test. Those who cannot take the test on that date may transfer to 
the March 19 testing date or have their fees refunded.HIGH SCHO 
