<HEADLINE>
<P>
PARTIAL LISTING OF DEATHS RELATED TO MONDAY'S QUAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles County Coroner's office said Thursday that 51 deaths are 
currently reported as being earthquake related, but the cause of many of the 
deaths will remain pending until full autopsies are completed and each case is 
reviewed. 
</P>
<P>
 Here are names of some of those who died. 
</P>
<P>
 Those who died in the collapse of the Northridge Meadows apartment building 
were: 
</P>
<P>
 Angeline (Ann) Cerone, 80; Sharon Englar, 58; Phil Englar, 62; Darla Raye 
Enos, 43; Pil Soon Lee, 46; Hwon Lee, 14; Cecilia Pressman, 72; David Pressman, 
72; Bea Reskin, 71; Jaime Reyes, 19; Karol Runnings, 48; Manuel D. Sandoval, 
24; Adam Slotnik, 27, and Myrna Velasquez, 18. 
</P>
<P>
 Others who died in the quake: 
</P>
<P>
 Jerry Borman, 67, Santa Clarita; Pearl Carr, 70, Granada Hills; Norman Cole, 
79, Granada Hills; Los Angeles Police Officer Clarence W. Dean, 46; Ted Peter 
Fichtner, 28; Leonard Glasser, described as in his 60s, no residence listed; 
Hannah Kamiya, 75, Los Angeles; Gennady Khytman, 45, West Hollywood; Burton 
Krell, 59, Northridge; Kevin C. Maher, 25, Sherman Oaks; Antonia Munoz, 66; 
John Nalls, 64, Sherman Oaks; Judith Ann Ng, 42, Van Nuys; Karen Osterholt, 30, 
Sherman Oaks; Robert Pauline, 72, Van Nuys; Concha Quintanar, 83, San Fernando; 
Madeline Riggins, 92, Panorama City; Maxfield Smith, 62, Marina del Rey; Amy 
Tyre-Vigil, 4, Sherman Oaks; Olga Robles Uribe, 26; Margarita Vasquez, 90; 
Lionel Ventura, 20, Sun Valley; Herbert Wesley, 45, Pico Rivera; Marc Yobs, 32, 
Sherman Oaks.. 
</P>
