<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / SADDLEBACK / SOUTH BEACH: SAN CLEMENTE; SENIOR ACCEPTED 
INTO HONOR BAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jamie Likely, a San Clemente High School senior, has been accepted into the 
1994 All-State Honor Band. 
</P>
<P>
 Likely, 17, is one of 250 students selected by taped auditions out of more 
than 600 applicants from around the state. 
</P>
<P>
 She will audition again Feb. 11 in Fresno, after which she will be placed in 
either the symphonic band directed by Tim Smith of Cal State Hayward, or the 
concert band led by Bill Johnson of Cal Poly San Luis Obispo. 
</P>
<P>
 After two days of concentrated rehearsals, the two bands will present concerts 
on Feb. 13 in the Saroyan Theater at the Fresno Convention Center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
