<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / NORTHWEST: LOS ALAMITOS; ANNUAL REPORTS ON SCHOOLS 
AVAILABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 School accountability report cards for all schools in the city are available 
to the community. 
</P>
<P>
 Mandated by state law, the annual reports are compiled by committees of 
teachers, administrators, parents, students and staff. 
</P>
<P>
 They assess and update school descriptions, academic performance, class size, 
teacher assignments, instruction, leadership, staff developments, curriculum 
improvements, teacher evaluations, funding, textbooks and other materials, 
substitute teachers, student services, attendance and dropout rates, school 
facilities, safety and salary information. 
</P>
<P>
 Copies of a school's report are available at each school, the Seal Beach and 
Rossmoor public libraries and the school district office, 10293 Bloomfield St., 
Los Alamitos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
