<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / NORTH: FULLERTON; INFORMATION DAY FOR AMPUTEES TO BE HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Amputee Information Day, a conference for people who have lost a limb, will be 
held Saturday at the Sequoia Athletic Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Sponsored by the Amputee Resource Center, the conference will feature 
presentations on prosthetic technology, relationships between patients and 
doctors, coping with limb loss and phantom pain, and techniques for enjoying 
sports after amputation. 
</P>
<P>
 Mary Novotny, president of the Amputee Coalition of America, will be the 
keynote speaker. She will address the ramifications of health care legislation 
on amputees. 
</P>
<P>
 The conference will be from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. at the athletic club, 1535 
Deerpark Drive, Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 There is no charge for the event, but reservations are required. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the Amputee Resource Center at (800) 244-2411. 
</P>
</TEXT>
