<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / NORTH: FULLERTON; LADERA VISTA PUPILS LAUNCH QUAKE DRIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Students at Ladera Vista Junior High School are in the midst of a drive to 
raise $1,000 to help victims of the recent earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 Teacher Andi Goettinger said students took coffee cans around the school 
Wednesday to collect money from teachers and other students. About $300 has 
been raised so far and the drive will continue through today, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Goettinger said students also raised about $1,000 after the Loma Prieta 
earthquake for victims in Northern California. All the money will go to the 
American Red Cross, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Students have been eager to raise money, Goettinger said. "As long as those 
aftershocks keep shaking, people are real interested." WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
