<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / COUNTYWIDE: FIREFIGHTER'S WIFE STARTS QUAKE DRIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Moved by the plight of earthquake victims forced to camp in parks, resident 
Stephanie Espinosa has organized a drive to collect goods through the Orange 
County Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
 "The thought that I couldn't diaper my baby or offer him juice just moved me 
more than I can express," said Espinosa, the wife of a Los Angeles firefighter 
who responded to the earthquake, and the mother of two boys. 
</P>
<P>
 Donations can be dropped off at four south Orange County fire stations: Laguna 
Hills Station 22, 24001 Paseo de Valencia; Lake Forest Station 19, 23022 El 
Toro Road; Mission Viejo Stations 24, 25862 Marguerite Parkway, and 31, 22426 
Olympiad Road. 
</P>
</TEXT>
