<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES: BRETHREN'S DAVIS PICKS WASHINGTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Reggie Davis, a defensive back at Brethren Christian High, made an oral 
commitment to Washington, Brethren Christian Coach Ken Sharrar said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis, a 6-foot-4, 200-pound senior, visited the Seattle campus last weekend 
and canceled trips to Nebraska, Wisconsin and Arizona State. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's the first defensive back to commit to Washington, so I think that says 
something," Sharrar said. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis, an All-Southern Section Division X selection, also played quarterback 
and helped the Warriors to the Division X championship game, where they lost to 
North Hills L.A. Baptist. MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
