<HEADLINE>
<P>
BULLFROGS' SCHEDULE SET; LEAGUE ALSO ANNOUNCES TV DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Bullfrogs will open the 1994 season and defense of their Roller Hockey 
International championship by playing host to the Los Angeles Blades June 4 at 
Anaheim Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 RHI also announced a television deal with ESPN and ESPN2.The cable networks 
will broadcast games each week, playoff games, the RHI all-star game and the 
championship series. 
</P>
<P>
 This announcement came shortly after RHI said it was merging with the World 
Roller Hockey League. RHI, which had 12 teams for its inaugural season in 1993, 
has expanded to 20 teams and hopes to add two to four franchises by Feb. 1. 
</P>
<P>
 New franchises are in Atlanta, Chicago, Edmonton, Minnesota, Montreal, New 
Jersey, Philadelphia, Pittsburgh, San Jose, and Tampa Bay. The Utah Rollerbees 
relocated to Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bullfrogs will play a 22-game schedule with 11 home dates. Single-game 
ticket prices range from $8 to $50, with season tickets available at up to a 
50% discount. 
</P>
<P>
 The 1994 schedule: 
</P>
<P>
 JUNE: 4 -- Los Angeles. 12 -- at Las Vegas. 17 -- Sacramento. 19 -- Oakland. 
23 -- San Jose. 25 -- at San Diego. 26 -- at Los Angeles. 29 -- Portland. 
</P>
<P>
 JULY: 2 -- at San Diego. 3 -- Oakland. 9 -- All-Star game, at Vancouver. 10 -- 
San Jose. 14 -- at Las Vegas. 15 -- at San Jose. 17 -- San Diego. 23 -- Los 
Angeles. 29 -- Las Vegas. 30 -- at Oakland. 
</P>
<P>
 AUG.: 2 -- Vancouver. 4 -- at Los Angeles. 6 -- at Arizona. 12 -- at Calgary. 
14 -- at Edmonton. 
</P>
