<TEXT>
<P>
 Apple Computer Inc. Profit Plunges: The Cupertino, Calif.-based company said 
first-quarter earnings dropped 75% despite record sales of its flagship 
Macintosh personal computers, as price competition ate into profit.Earnings in 
the quarter ended Dec. 31 shrank to $40 million from $161.3 million a year ago, 
and gross margins fell to 24% of net sales from 40.5%, Apple said. Per-share 
earnings tumbled to 34 cents from $1.33. 
</P>
