<TEXT>
<P>
 Saturn Workers to Get Bonuses: General Motors Corp. said its 8,543 Saturn 
workers will receive payments of about $2,867 at the end of the month, 
reflecting the division's ability to meet its quality and productivity goals 
while earning a profit last year.Under Saturn's innovative labor agreement with 
the United Auto Workers union, employees are rewarded for meeting certain 
targets. Employees must also complete 92 hours of training a year in order to 
bring their base pay to the same level as other auto workers'. Saturn employees 
received about $5,100 in reward payments in 1993. 
</P>
