</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fixed-Rate Mortgage Rate Rises to 7.05%: The average interest rate on the 
30-year loans rose this week from 6.99% last week, the Federal Home Loan 
Mortgage Corp. said.The figure is still below the recent peak of 7.31% reached 
in late November. The average hit a 25-year low of 6.74% in October. 
Fifteen-year mortgages, an increasingly popular option, averaged 6.57% this 
week, up from 6.48% a week earlier. On one-year, adjustable-rate mortgages, 
lenders were asking an average initial rate of 4.24%, up from 4.20% last week. 
The rates do not include points. 
</P>
