<P>
 Price/Costco to Shut Four Stores: Closing Jan. 30 are a Costco store in 
Riverside and Price Club stores in Bakersfield; Richmond, Calif., and New 
Britain, Conn.As many as 350 employees may be affected, said Richard Galanti, 
Price/Costco's chief financial officer. The stores were targeted for closure 
because they are in markets that overlap with other stores as a result of last 
year's $2.3-billion merger of Kirkland, Wash.-based Costco Wholesale Corp. and 
San Diego-based Price Inc. No further closures are planned, Galanti said. 
</P>
