<TEXT>
<P>
 Viacom May Sue Paramount: In a letter to Paramount Communications Inc., Viacom 
Inc. formally notified the company that it is reserving the right to sue for 
the $100-million breakup fee originally negotiated in a friendly merger deal in 
September. That merger agreement was scrapped Dec. 22 after the Paramount board 
decided to recommend a QVC Network Inc. bid to its shareholders instead. 
However, Viacom said it will not pursue the legal action while Paramount is in 
the midst of its auction. 
