<P>
 Pacific Telesis Posts $391-Million 4th-Quarter Loss: The company attributed 
the loss of 92 cents a share for the period ended Dec 31. largely to 
restructuring costs.A year earlier, Pacific Telesis earned $287 million, or 71 
cents per share. Revenue was $2.3 billion, up 1% from $2.27 billion in the 
fourth quarter of 1992. Its earnings for the latest period were reduced by $670 
million because of special onetime charges for a restructuring that is expected 
to eliminate 10,000 jobs by the end of 1997. Without the charges, the company 
said, it would have earned $279 million, or 66 cents a share, which is still 
below its performance a year ago. 
