<P>
 Pacific Bell Announces Telecommuting Relief Package: With Los Angeles-area 
residents facing nightmarish traffic because of earthquake damage to freeways, 
Pacific Bell announced a package intended to make it easier for workers to 
operate from home. The phone company said that for the next month it will waive 
installation charges on more than a dozen services for customers in the 818, 
805, 213, 310, 714 and 909 area codes and is setting up a hot line for help and 
referrals, which will operate from 8 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Monday through 
Friday.The company is also donating $1 million to fund loans of telecommuting 
equipment. GTE also announced plans to offer a wide array of telecommuting 
options to the public, but it does not yet have PUC approval. It also plans to 
waive certain fees. 
