<HEADLINE>
<P>
CASTLE ROCK ELEVATES LIZ GLOTZER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Castle Rock Entertainment named Liz Glotzer to the new post of president of 
production, overseeing development and production at the maker of such films as 
"In the Line of Fire," "A Few Good Men," "City Slickers" and the upcoming 
"North." 
</P>
<P>
 The move is a sign of formerly independent Castle Rock's desire to boost 
production now that the production company is owned by Turner Broadcasting 
System.Glotzer has been with Castle Rock since it was founded in 1987 and most 
recently was vice president of production. "This sends a signal (that Glotzer) 
is the person they can look to for answers in terms of development," Castle 
Rock President Martin Shafer said. The company plans to boost output to up to 
seven films in '94, possibly to 12 within a few years. 
</P>
