<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: ROCKWELL FORMS CHINA VENTURE TO MAKE PRESS EQUIPMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rockwell International Corp., the $11-billion diversified technology giant, 
said Thursday that it has formed a joint venture to produce printing-press 
equipment in the People's Republic of China. 
</P>
<P>
 Rockwell's Graphic Systems business in Westmont, Ill., will team up with the 
Shanghai Printing and Packaging Machinery Corp. in Shanghai. Rockwell, based in 
Seal Beach, has licensed its printing technology to a subsidiary of the Chinese 
company since 1984. 
</P>
